s. Through an examination of Maoists, Socialists, Euro-Communists, and pro-Soviet groups, it demonstrates that left-wing youth in Greece collaborated closely with comrades from both Western and Eastern European countries in developing their political stances. Moreover, young left-wingers in Greece appropriated American cultural products while simultaneously modeling some of their leisure and sexual practices on Soviet society. Still, despite being heavily influenced by cultures outside Greece, left-wing youth played a major role in the reinvention of a Greek “popular tradition.” This book critically interrogates the notion of “sexual revolution” by shedding light on the contradictory sexual transformations in Greece to which young left-wingers contributed.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Nov 2022) 0aLeisurexPolitical aspectszGreecexHistoryy20th century. 0aNew LeftzGreecexHistoryy20th century. 0aPolitical activistszGreecexHistoryy20th century. 0aPolitical culturezGreecexHistoryy20th century. 0aSocial changezGreecexHistoryy20th century. 0aYouthxPolitical activityzGreecexHistoryy20th century. 0aYouthxSexual behaviorzGreecexHistoryy20th century. 0aYouthzGreecexSocial conditionsy20th century. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Greece (see also Ancient / Greece).2bisacsh  aGreece.  aGreek History.  aGreek Youth.  aLeft-Wing Politics.  aYouth Politics.  aYouth Studies, Political Activism.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBerghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311099823840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781782386452?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781782386452423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781782386452/original  a978-3-11-099823-8  Berghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS